title: The Watch House
description: Erected 1826. Brick with stone string course at 1st floor sill level inscribed with date of erection and churchwardens' names. Ground floor has 2 rusticated and vermiculated brick and stone arches with window and door in recessed brick panels. Stone coped parapet and stone plinth. Two storeys, two windows under flat gauged arches. Glazing bars to those of upper storey. Included for historical and social interest.
